    {
      "id": "PopularPost343518",
      "post_content": "If I had to choose between this and [Pillar of Flame](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pillar of Flame), I'd play this because instant speed is far better than sorcery. And if my deck needs this kind of effect, it means that what it want the most is the exile effect. If it weren't so, I would play [Shock](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shock) without any other thought. Or [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt), for the matter. However, if dealing damage to player is something non-negotiable, then I would suggest you to look for [Carbonize](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Carbonize) or [Yamabushi's Flame](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Yamabushi's Flame), it depends from the format...  \n  \n4/5",
      "posted_by": "leomistico",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost343518\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">If I had to choose between this and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Pillar of Flame\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pillar of Flame\">Pillar of Flame</a>, I'd play this because instant speed is far better than sorcery. And if my deck needs this kind of effect, it means that what it want the most is the exile effect. If it weren't so, I would play <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Shock\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shock\">Shock</a> without any other thought. Or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Lightning Bolt\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a>, for the matter. However, if dealing damage to player is something non-negotiable, then I would suggest you to look for <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Carbonize\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Carbonize\">Carbonize</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Yamabushi's Flame\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Yamabushi's Flame\">Yamabushi's Flame</a>, it depends from the format...<br/><br/>4/5</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '343518'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy822\">leomistico</span>\r\n          